1. Exercise 1: Clearly explains the purpose of the chmod command and how it relates to file permissions in Linux (1 point).
2. Exercise 1: Provides the correct chmod commands and usage to set the specified file permissions (1 point).
3. Exercise 2: Describes the purpose of user groups in Linux and how they relate to file access (1 point).
4. Exercise 2: Correctly explains the steps to create a new user, add them to a group, and set file permissions for that group (1 point).
5. Exercise 3: Describes the importance of logging and monitoring file access in Linux, and explains how to enable file access logging (1 point).

Note: Each requirement must be explicitly addressed in the "Theoretical background" section in order to receive credit. A requirement will not be given credit if it is only demonstrated in the exercises, but not explained in the theoretical background.